<br>
I want to take a stab at it too.  *smirk*<br>
<br>
I don't believe in a soul.  I don't believe in the dangers of desire, only the dangers of being caught enacting them foolishly. I don't believe in the supposed sanctity of self-restraint for it's own sake, nor do I believe in the fear of fearing death.<br>
<br>
I believe that excessive desire, unrequited love, desperate romanticisms in general are spawned in the hearts of those people who have little else to do.  I believe that I live to hunger, I live to feed, I live to devour and love and mate and die.  I am born in flesh, I live in flesh, I will die and decay in flesh; the nature in which I live and breathe is sublime.  It is not necessary to contrive some silly notion that I exist for any other reason - the wetness of my eyes and the warmth of my body is enough.<br>
<br>
The greatest forces behind life are Thanatos and Eros.  I agree with Freude on that one.  When I am sated in both these aspects, when I have fed and made love and am well-rested, I am almost at peace.  These drives innervate me, and whatever act I may take to sate them is justified and good because it is mine.  If it is contrary to society, I accept the consequences.  &quot;Do as you will to satiate desire, but keep in mind the policeman around the corner.&quot;<br>
<br>
I also do not believe in Peace, in regards to an absolute.  I think the hope for peace is more damaging than the fear of eternal dischord.  I don't have any faith in humanity, when it comes to gentleness.<br>
<br>
*My Point*<br>
<br>
Personal philosophies, whether they are eloquently put or stated in a vulgar and condescending manner , are simply that - personal.  And I put no stock in them.  Speaking your personal theories on life to a stranger is rude, I think.  Sharing them with a loved one is amusing and rather charming but also pointless, save it makes conversation.  These are dreams.  Dreams mean nothing, save to yourself.  Why shovel them into the ditch of what they mean, or seek approval from others upon retelling them, or even worse attempt to preach your own?<br>
<br>
By posting this, I invalidate my own belief that this is stupid, I know =).  I am bored.<br>
